<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,150,501]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,187,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
In 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[357,663,187,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, the sexual gall is named as ‘Kunugi-hana-ko-kuro-tama-fushi’ (C- 098), while the asexual gall is named as ‘Kunugi-ha-ke-tsubo-tama-fushi’ (C-091), ‘abemaki-ha-ura-ke-tsubo-tamafushi’ (C-047) and is also shown without a name (C-092, the gall at right). 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Sala-Nishikawa, A. &amp; Melika, G." box="[1002,1313,259,285]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="515 - 528" refId="ref51602" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Guo, R., Sala-Nishikawa, A. &amp; Melika, G. (2020 d) A new species of Cerroneuroterus Melika &amp; Pujade-Villar from Eastern Palaearctic (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae, Cynipini). Zootaxa, 4869 (4), 515 - 528. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4869.4.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[1160,1210,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. (2020d)
</bibRefCitation>
concluded that those galls correspond to a new species, named 
<emphasis box="[736,1117,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pujade-Villar &amp; Melika" authorityYear="2020" box="[736,1113,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Cerroneuroterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yukawamasudai">Cerroneuroterus yukawamasudai</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,150,501]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,412,330,357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks (2). The</emphasis>
asexual females were described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Sala-Nishikawa, A. &amp; Melika, G." box="[827,1145,331,357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="515 - 528" refId="ref51602" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Guo, R., Sala-Nishikawa, A. &amp; Melika, G. (2020 d) A new species of Cerroneuroterus Melika &amp; Pujade-Villar from Eastern Palaearctic (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae, Cynipini). Zootaxa, 4869 (4), 515 - 528. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4869.4.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[985,1037,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. (2020d)
</bibRefCitation>
. T 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1174,1202,331,357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">he</emphasis>
alternating lifecycle was closed, and the sexual and asexual galls were described, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[869,1169,367,393]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,150,501]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,402,428]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Biology.</emphasis>
The catkin galls of the sexual generation and the detachable leaf galls of the asexual generation both develop on 
<taxonomicName box="[286,442,439,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutissima">
<emphasis box="[286,442,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Q. acutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[500,643,439,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[500,643,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Q. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[721,793,439,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cerris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[721,793,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Cerris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[920,1207,439,465]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Sala-Nishikawa, A. &amp; Melika, G." pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="515 - 528" refId="ref51602" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Guo, R., Sala-Nishikawa, A. &amp; Melika, G. (2020 d) A new species of Cerroneuroterus Melika &amp; Pujade-Villar from Eastern Palaearctic (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae, Cynipini). Zootaxa, 4869 (4), 515 - 528. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4869.4.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[1378,1429,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2020d
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
